sec.p:
There are various difference equations for the pressure distribution calculation. The following four types are compared in this section:


equation derived directly from the continuity equation (shown in the ‘Numerical analysis’ section);

the standard form of the elliptic-type equation, developed from the Reynolds equation;

Southwell’s25 relaxation; and

modified Southwell’s relaxation.

Method (b) involves convergence problems. While the other three methods showed convergence in all the computing points, method (b) diverged at the following computing points:


for grid 60 × 60 (L/R > 1.2, a < 0.05), (L/R > 2, a < 0.1), (L/R > 2.5, a < 0.15), (L/R > 3, a < 0.2), (L/R > 4, a < 0.25) with ω = 1.9;

for grid 120 × 120 (L/R > 2, a < 0.05, ω = 1.8), (L/R > 4, a < 0.1 ω = 1.8);

for grid 180 × 180 (L/R > 3, a < 0.05, ω = 1.8); and

for grid 240 × 240 (L > R > 6, a < 0.05, ω = 1.8).
